{"ts": "2026-06-07T10:15:42.000Z", "event": "planner", "msg": "L2 task decomposition", "agent": "planner-l2", "tokens_in": 384, "tokens_out": 448, "elapsed_ms": 4879, "model": "qwen/qwen3-235b-a22b-2507", "prompt": "You are the Level 2 Planner. Decompose the user task into subtasks.\n\nOutput JSON:\n{{\n  \"subtasks\": [\n    {{\"task_id\": \"short-name\", \"description\": \"What this worker must produce\"}}\n  ]\n}}\n\nRules:\n- Each subtask should be a focused, self-contained unit of work\n- Include file names and output expectations in descriptions\n- For simple tasks, 2-3 subtasks; for complex tasks, 4-6\n- FRONTEND: Always include an index.html (main entry page). Additional pages\n  (hero.html, about.html, etc.) are fine, but index.html must exist and link to them.\n  Subtask descriptions should specify what content/sections each file contains.\n- Output ONLY the JSON object — no markdown fences\n\n## Specialty\nfrontend\n\n## User Request\nBuild an accessible landing page for a non-profit environmental organization called \"GreenFuture\". Deliver as index.html, styles.css, app.js, and a11y_report.md.\n\nThe page must be fully conformant with WCAG 2.1 Level AA. Specific requirements:\n- All images have descriptive alt text (not empty, not \"image\")\n- All form inputs have associated <label> with for attribute\n- Heading hierarchy is sequential: h1 → h2 → h3 (never skip levels)\n- All text has minimum color contrast ratio of 4.5:1 against background\n- A \"Skip to main content\" link is the first focusable element\n- All interactive elements (buttons, links, form controls) are keyboard-accessible\n- Use semantic HTML5: <header>, <nav>, <main>, <section>, <footer>\n- ARIA labels where semantic elements are insufficient\n\nDeliver a11y_report.md listing every accessibility rule applied and how it was implemented.", "meta": {}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T10:16:59.000Z", "event": "agent_creator", "msg": "Agent Creator L2 — generating workers", "agent": "agent-creator-l2", "tokens_in": 1365, "tokens_out": 783, "elapsed_ms": 77195, "model": "qwen/qwen3-235b-a22b-2507", "prompt": "You are the Agent Creator (Level 2 — Template-Based). Your role: create worker agent configurations by selecting from predefined templates.\n\n## Available Templates for this Specialty\n[\n  {\n    \"name\": \"ux\",\n    \"role\": \"ux_designer\",\n    \"system_prompt\": \"You are a UX/UI Content Designer. Generate real content, copy, and image prompts for the web page. Save as content_brief.json.\",\n    \"default_tools\": [\n      \"read_file\",\n      \"write_file\",\n      \"list_files\",\n      \"generate_image\"\n    ],\n    \"skill_paths\": []\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"html\",\n    \"role\": \"html_developer\",\n    \"system_prompt\": \"You are an HTML Developer. Write semantic HTML5. Save as index.html. Use write_file ONLY.\",\n    \"default_tools\": [\n      \"read_file\",\n      \"write_file\",\n      \"list_files\",\n      \"validate_html\",\n      \"render_html_file_screenshot\",\n      \"generate_image\",\n      \"run_command\"\n    ],\n    \"skill_paths\": [\n      \"frontend/accessibility.json\"\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"css\",\n    \"role\": \"css_developer\",\n    \"system_prompt\": \"You are a CSS Developer. Write modern CSS with variables, flexbox, grid. Save as styles.css. Use write_file ONLY.\",\n    \"default_tools\": [\n      \"read_file\",\n      \"write_file\",\n      \"list_files\",\n      \"validate_css\",\n      \"run_command\"\n    ],\n    \"skill_paths\": [\n      \"frontend/css_styling.json\"\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"js\",\n    \"role\": \"js_developer\",\n    \"system_prompt\": \"You are a JavaScript Developer. Write vanilla ES6+ JS. Save as app.js. Use write_file ONLY.\",\n    \"default_tools\": [\n      \"read_file\",\n      \"write_file\",\n      \"list_files\",\n      \"run_command\"\n    ],\n    \"skill_paths\": [\n      \"frontend/accessibility.json\"\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"tester\",\n    \"role\": \"frontend_tester\",\n    \"system_prompt\": \"You are a Frontend Tester. Validate HTML, CSS, JS files. Write test_report.json with structured issues.\",\n    \"default_tools\": [\n      \"read_file\",\n      \"write_file\",\n      \"list_files\",\n      \"validate_html\",\n      \"validate_css\",\n      \"render_html_file_screenshot\",\n      \"read_image\",\n      \"run_command\"\n    ],\n    \"skill_paths\": [\n      \"tester/e2e_testing.json\"\n    ]\n  }\n]\n\n## Available Tools\nThe tool menu for this specialty:\n[\"read_file\", \"write_file\", \"list_files\", \"run_command\", \"render_html_screenshot\", \"render_html_file_screenshot\", \"validate_html\", \"validate_css\", \"read_image\", \"generate_image\"]\n\n## Task Plan\nThe planner has decomposed the task into subtasks:\n{\n  \"subtasks\": [\n    {\n      \"task_id\": \"scaffold-files\",\n      \"description\": \"Create the initial project files: index.html, styles.css, app.js, and a11y_report.md. Set up basic HTML5 structure in index.html with doctype, lang attribute, charset, viewport meta, and proper linking to CSS and JS assets.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"task_id\": \"build-structure\",\n      \"description\": \"Implement semantic HTML5 structure in index.html: include a 'Skip to main content' link as the first focusable element, <header>, <nav>, <main>, multiple <section> elements (hero, mission, programs, donate), and <footer>. Ensure correct heading hierarchy (h1 \\u2192 h2 \\u2192 h3) and add placeholder content with descriptive alt text for all images.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"task_id\": \"style-accessible-ui\",\n      \"description\": \"Write CSS in styles.css to style the page with WCAG 2.1 AA compliance: ensure all text-background combinations meet minimum 4.5:1 contrast ratio, use relative units, and style focus indicators for keyboard navigation. Do not use color alone to convey information.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"task_id\": \"implement-interactivity\",\n      \"description\": \"Add keyboard accessibility and ARIA enhancements in app.js: ensure all interactive elements (navigation, donate button, form) are operable via keyboard, manage focus where needed, and add ARIA labels when semantic HTML is insufficient. Include a simple donation form with properly associated <label> elements using 'for' and 'id' attributes.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"task_id\": \"generate-a11y-report\",\n      \"description\": \"Populate a11y_report.md with a checklist of all WCAG 2.1 Level AA requirements addressed: document use of semantic HTML, alt text, heading structure, color contrast, keyboard navigation, labels, skip link, and ARIA. For each rule, describe how it was implemented in the code (e.g., 'Skip to main content: first tabbable element with href=\\\"#main\\\"').\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n\n## Your Job\nFor EACH subtask in the plan:\n1. Pick the BEST matching template from the available templates above\n2. Optionally EDIT the system_prompt to add task-specific details (file names, specific requirements)\n3. Select a SUBSET of tools from the available tool menu that the worker needs\n4. Set skill_paths from the template\n\n## Rules\n- Output ONLY valid JSON — no markdown fences, no extra text\n- worker_name MUST match a template name (or be \"tester\")\n- system_prompt: start from the template prompt, then add task-specific instructions\n- tool_names: only pick from the available tool menu\n- skill_paths: copy the template's skill_paths or leave empty\n- FRONTEND FILE NAMES: The html worker always outputs index.html (the main page).\n  The css worker always outputs styles.css. The js worker always outputs app.js.\n  Additional HTML pages (hero.html, about.html, etc.) are fine but index.html\n  is the canonical main entry. Add section-specific instructions to the prompt,\n  do NOT rename the output file.\n\n## Output Format\n{\n  \"workers\": [\n    {\n      \"worker_name\": \"template_name\",\n      \"system_prompt\": \"Full customized system instructions for the worker\",\n      \"tool_names\": [\"tool1\", \"tool2\"],\n      \"skill_paths\": [\"path/to/skill.json\"]\n    }\n  ]\n}", "meta": {}}
